thread.title: Hillbillies' strong play continues as winning-streak hits six

title: Hillbillies' strong play continues as winning-streak hits six
text:
Buy this photo thinkstock 
Back-to-back wins over West Orange and Dayton increased the Verona girls volleyball team's winning streak to six. The Hillbillies defeated West Orange in two sets Saturday, Oct. 3 before their two-set victory over Dayton Monday, Oct. 5. 
Verona won the first set over West Orange 25-15 and closed the door with a 35-17 showing in the second set. Sophomore Carly Waterman led the Hillbillies with 12 digs and 17 kills. Sophomore Madisyn Matthews recorded a team-high 11 assists, with junior Catie Kenneally not far behind with nine. 
Verona's contest against Dayton was a bit closer, though the Hillbillies still swept the two sets. Verona won the opening round 26-24 before closing the door on Dayton with a 25-15 second-set victory. Sophomore libero Cameron Fuentez recorded a team-high six digs in the win. Waterman led Verona with 16 kills, while Kenneally finished with a team-leading nine assists.
